The paper discusses a framework for efficient clustering algorithms, which falls under the category of machine learning and data mining. The use of spectral clustering and the focus on performance and runtime complexity suggest that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. However, the paper also deals with data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and information retrieval (cs.IR), which are all related to clustering. Additionally, the use of large datasets and the need for efficient storage and processing suggest that cs.DB (Databases) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are also possible sub-categories.
